# Contacts extension build-time OAuth credentials.
#
# These values are injected into the extensions/contacts package vars
# (GoogleClientID, GoogleClientSecret, MicrosoftClientID) at build time via
# ldflags. Copy this file to .env (gitignored) and fill in your project values
# OR leave it empty and let the user supply credentials at runtime via
# Settings -> Extensions -> Contacts -> OAuth Credentials.
#
# Make process consumes this file when the Contacts extension is enabled in
# the build. See Makefile target build-extensions.
#
# Google OAuth project for Contacts WRITE scope
# (https://www.googleapis.com/auth/contacts).
# Aerion's contacts READ continues to ride mail OAuth — this project ONLY
# requests write scope and is verified independently from the mail project.
GOOGLE_CONTACTS_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CONTACTS_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Microsoft Azure AD app registration for Contacts.ReadWrite scope.
# Typically the SAME value as Aerion core's MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID — Microsoft
# permits scope additions to an existing AAD registration without re-review.
# Desktop OAuth uses PKCE, no client secret.
MICROSOFT_CONTACTS_CLIENT_ID=
